    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PROFIT RISES AT BRITISH BANK</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>HSBC Holdings PLC reports pretax profit rose 28 percent, Jan-June, to $5.2 billion (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>HSBC Holdings P.L.C. said pretax profit rose 28 percent in the first half of the year, to $5.2 billion. The results, which beat analysts expectations, come as HSBC is beginning to integrate its many recent acquisitions including Republic New York. HSBC said its earnings were buoyed by growth in markets across Europe, Asia, North America and Latin America despite intense pressure on margins in Britain.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
